result.execSummary:
The defendant Dustin J. GENZ was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Obstruct officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

The matter was set for a hearing to modify the sentence.  The defendant has not completed his community service as ordered by the court.
The defendant explains why he didn't do the community service.  He has completed ten hours at Maribel Caves.
The Court will give the defendant an additional 30 days to complete it.  If not completed, the court will imposed ten (10) days in the county jail.  The defendant is to bring proof of completion with him.  The defendant states he understands.
Motion hearing is reset to 10-06-15 at 11:00 a.m.

The State moves to amend the charge to obstruct officer, contrary to Section 946.41(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  Motion granted.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge.  Convicted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for four (4) months, under the Huber Law, commencing on 04-22-15 by 8:30 a.m.  Court authorizes transfer to either Brown County or Kewaunee County Jail or in the alternative, Court authorizes travel to Kewaunee County for employment purposes and orders that travel time be excluded when calculating Huber release.
$443.00 court costs imposed, to be paid by 04-25-15 or 9 days county jail for failure to pay.
The defendant has 3 days credit.
